textBody:
KSL may refer to:

Companies and organizations

* KSL (radio) — KSL-AM and KSL-FM — radio stations in Utah, United States
* KSL-TV, a TV station in Utah, United States 
* KSL Holdings Bhd, a property developer in Malaysia 
* Key Sounds Label, a Japanese record label
* Knights of St Lazarus, a medieval Catholic military ordet
* Knowledge Systems Laboratory, an artificial intelligence research lab at Stanford

Locations and transportation

* Kate Sharpley Library, a library of anarchist publications 
* Kearsley railway station, England
* Kowloon Southern Link, a section of the MTR West Rail Line in Hong Kong
* KSL City, a shopping mall/residential/hotel complex in Johor, Malaysia 

Other

* Kenyan Sign Language
* Korean Sign Language
* KSL cells, early form of hematopoietic stem cells
